WEBVTT

00:06.780 --> 00:08.279
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>Masters Of Sex...</i>

00:08.281 --> 00:09.414
Nora: Say you love me.

00:09.449 --> 00:11.082
William: - I'm sorry.
Nora: - I want this.

00:11.117 --> 00:12.166
William:
It-- it was a mistake.

00:12.202 --> 00:14.419
I made-- I made a mistake.

00:14.454 --> 00:15.620
Nora: I should go.

00:15.622 --> 00:16.704
Ronald:
You don't have to tell me

00:16.756 --> 00:18.039
how you've strayed
from the path.

00:18.091 --> 00:20.008
I just want to be sure
you're ready to return to it.

00:20.043 --> 00:23.094
Betty: Your ultrasound technician,
Jonathan, handed me his notice.

00:23.129 --> 00:24.178
Barton:
It wasn't the right fit.

00:24.214 --> 00:25.513
Betty:
I'm surprised to hear that.

00:25.548 --> 00:27.682
I thought you two
had a real nice rapport.

00:27.717 --> 00:29.801
William: I'm having dreams
about my father.

00:29.803 --> 00:31.436
Old man: You've got to pull
yourself together.

00:31.471 --> 00:32.686
If you can't control yourself,

00:32.722 --> 00:34.439
how are you
gonna get control of <i> her?</i>

00:34.474 --> 00:36.357
Paul: - I want you to be my wife.
Libby: - There's a lot

00:36.393 --> 00:38.109
that would need to happen
to make that possible.

00:38.144 --> 00:40.545
Paul: You have to get out.
Get out before Bill comes home.

00:40.580 --> 00:41.946
Libby: I can't do that, Paul.

00:41.982 --> 00:45.116
David: Johnny, have you ever
seen your father and Dennis

00:45.151 --> 00:46.818
have any kind
of physical contact--

00:46.870 --> 00:48.820
Libby: Okay,
that is enough, Detective.

00:48.822 --> 00:50.989
William: Masters and Johnson.

00:50.991 --> 00:52.323
It's who we are.

00:52.325 --> 00:53.925
You know,
it's how people think of us.

00:53.960 --> 00:55.259
It's how we think of ourselves.

00:55.295 --> 00:57.562
Dan: There's a far easier way
to get what you want.

00:57.597 --> 00:58.663
William: Which is what?

00:58.698 --> 00:59.897
Dan: Tell her
how you feel about her.

00:59.933 --> 01:01.232
William: Libby had her
track me down.

01:01.267 --> 01:03.167
Something's happened.
I need to get home.

01:03.169 --> 01:04.936
Alice: When he shows up
at your doorstep

01:05.004 --> 01:08.222
and tells you that he wants you to
spend the rest of your life with him,

01:08.258 --> 01:09.974
he will think he means it.

