01:56.272 --> 01:58.973
[ Crowd cheering ]

02:01.895 --> 02:03.895
[ Cheers and applause ]

02:03.947 --> 02:05.363
Man: Ooh!

02:05.398 --> 02:07.448
Johnny: Hit him!
Come on, you bum!

02:07.484 --> 02:09.616
Old man:
Save your breath, son.

02:09.651 --> 02:12.303
This one-sided paint job
got no chance.

02:14.407 --> 02:16.741
Johnny:
I just don't see his strategy.

02:16.793 --> 02:19.911
Old man: Using his head to block
punches-- that's his strategy.

02:19.963 --> 02:20.945
[ Laughs ]

02:23.717 --> 02:26.884
Ugh, what a catcher
this Masters bum is.

02:26.920 --> 02:28.386
Get off the ropes!

02:28.421 --> 02:30.805
- Down he goes.
Referee: - One...

02:30.840 --> 02:32.757
Two...

02:32.759 --> 02:34.859
Johnny: - You're a bum, Masters!
Referee: - Three...

02:34.894 --> 02:36.811
Four...

02:36.846 --> 02:38.162
Five...

02:38.198 --> 02:39.964
Old man: Stay down.
You're beat.

02:41.434 --> 02:43.851
A man's got to know
when he's beat, son.

02:43.903 --> 02:45.520
A man has got to learn.

02:45.572 --> 02:47.105
Man: Stay down!

02:47.157 --> 02:49.273
Old man:
Nothing but a damn fool.

02:49.275 --> 02:50.658
Johnny: Goddamn fool.

02:50.693 --> 02:53.511
[ Crowd stomping rhythmically ]

02:58.201 --> 02:59.333
William: [ Gasping ]

02:59.369 --> 03:01.285
[ Breathing heavily ]

03:01.287 --> 03:02.837
- [ Gasps ]
Libby: - Bill, Bill.

03:02.872 --> 03:04.956
Bill, it's okay.
It's okay.

03:07.043 --> 03:10.061
Was it your father again?

03:10.096 --> 03:12.597
William: I'm not sure.

03:12.632 --> 03:15.633
Maybe.

03:15.685 --> 03:18.603
Libby:
I'm not surprised, considering.

03:18.638 --> 03:21.405
We can make this go away, Bill.

03:21.441 --> 03:22.807
William: I'm fine.
I'm fine.

03:22.809 --> 03:25.693
[ Sniffs, sighs ]

03:27.580 --> 03:31.232
Virginia: Lisa sleeps and eats,
essentially.

03:31.284 --> 03:32.817
Tessa's schedule
is a bit more complicated,

03:32.869 --> 03:35.119
although she can be very helpful
with the baby

03:35.155 --> 03:38.039
when she wants to be,
so insist that she pitch in.

03:38.074 --> 03:39.824
Harry:
Your mother's a little hurt

03:39.826 --> 03:42.326
you only asked me up here
to babysit.

03:42.378 --> 03:44.295
Virginia:
I have enough on my plate

03:44.330 --> 03:47.331
without adding mom's criticisms
to the pile.

03:47.333 --> 03:49.584
Harry: All right.

03:49.636 --> 03:53.304
Although usually when things get
tough, you dig in all the more.

03:53.339 --> 03:54.839
It's not like you to flee.

03:54.874 --> 03:56.257
Virginia: I'm not fleeing.

03:56.309 --> 03:57.475
I'm...

03:57.510 --> 03:58.576
Harry: Fleeing.

03:58.611 --> 04:00.478
Virginia:
...clearing my head...

04:00.513 --> 04:02.897
for a few days.

04:02.932 --> 04:04.065
Harry: Because?

04:04.100 --> 04:06.100
Virginia: Because...

04:06.152 --> 04:07.568
Well, to be perfectly honest,

04:07.604 --> 04:10.071
because I don't know
who to trust anymore.

04:10.106 --> 04:11.906
Harry: You can't trust Bill?

04:11.941 --> 04:13.691
Virginia: Especially Bill.

04:13.693 --> 04:16.994
I mean, he barreled ahead
with a surrogacy program

04:17.029 --> 04:18.495
against my wishes,

04:18.531 --> 04:22.116
and then he ambushed me at this
disastrous dinner in New York.

04:22.168 --> 04:23.367
And then the man that I'm seeing

04:23.419 --> 04:25.837
is making me
all kinds of promises--

04:25.872 --> 04:27.788
none of which
may actually be true.

04:27.841 --> 04:29.674
Harry: The man you're seeing.

04:29.709 --> 04:33.444
In addition to Bill.

04:37.717 --> 04:39.350
Virginia: [ Sighs ]

04:39.385 --> 04:41.586
Please, daddy.

04:41.621 --> 04:43.187
I know that my life is something

04:43.223 --> 04:46.557
that few people
would understand...

04:46.559 --> 04:50.361
And most would consider
a shambles.

04:50.396 --> 04:53.431
I'm not even sure
that I disagree, but...

04:53.466 --> 04:56.567
Harry: So it's good
you're getting away.

04:56.569 --> 04:59.737
And the girls and I
will be fine.

04:59.739 --> 05:02.406
You will be, too.

05:02.458 --> 05:03.624
Fine, I mean.

05:03.660 --> 05:05.910
Virginia: Oh, I don't know.

05:05.912 --> 05:09.714
I just keep waiting
for everything to...

05:09.749 --> 05:11.716
click into place.

05:11.751 --> 05:16.337
So I can say, finally, my life

05:16.389 --> 05:19.257
is exactly as it should be.

05:22.061 --> 05:25.897
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:25.932 --> 05:27.565
[ Door opens ]

05:27.600 --> 05:31.502
Oh.
Uh... I thought it was the taxi.

05:31.537 --> 05:34.655
Libby: I apologize
for the early hour, but I am--

05:34.691 --> 05:36.240
Are you leaving?

05:36.276 --> 05:38.242
Virginia: Briefly.

05:38.278 --> 05:40.444
I just need to sort out...

05:40.530 --> 05:42.830
What is it, Lib?
Is this about--

05:42.865 --> 05:44.448
Libby: Why I called Bill home?
Yes.

05:44.450 --> 05:46.083
Um, something's happened.

05:46.119 --> 05:49.120
Virginia:
With the kids or with Bill?

05:49.122 --> 05:51.005
Libby:
To all of us in a way.

05:51.040 --> 05:53.457
Something that could even affect
the future of the clinic.

05:53.459 --> 05:57.595
It always comes down to the two
of us, doesn't it, Gin?

05:57.630 --> 06:00.464
The two that can right the ship.

06:02.185 --> 06:07.138
♪

06:07.140 --> 06:09.523
Jonathan: It seems no one ever
taught you the proper etiquette

06:09.559 --> 06:10.741
of spending the night.

06:10.777 --> 06:14.111
You know, it is customary
after a romantic evening,

06:14.147 --> 06:16.080
to exchange pleasantries--

06:16.115 --> 06:19.650
"Good morning" or "I had
a lovely time with you.

06:19.686 --> 06:22.203
Let's do it again"
before sneaking out the door.

06:22.238 --> 06:23.788
Barton:
I didn't want to wake you.

06:23.823 --> 06:25.656
Jonathan: That isn't one
of the pleasantries.

06:25.692 --> 06:27.908
Barton:
I had a lovely time with you.

06:27.961 --> 06:29.393
Let's do it again.

06:30.930 --> 06:32.330
Also...

06:35.218 --> 06:38.569
I like you very much.

06:40.673 --> 06:44.175
Jonathan: Then stay.
Have breakfast.

06:44.177 --> 06:45.593
Barton:
I should go home and change.

06:45.645 --> 06:47.928
I think it's unwise
to show up to work

06:47.981 --> 06:50.314
wearing the same clothes
as yesterday.

06:50.350 --> 06:52.183
Jonathan: Well, you can borrow
one of my ties.

06:52.185 --> 06:53.234
Barton: Mm-hmm.

06:53.269 --> 06:54.685
Jonathan:
You're not gonna leave me

06:54.687 --> 06:57.488
to have breakfast by myself
on my birthday, are you?

06:57.523 --> 06:59.240
Barton: Your birthday?

06:59.275 --> 07:01.158
I had no idea!

07:01.194 --> 07:03.411
Why don't we celebrate tonight,
properly?

07:03.446 --> 07:07.448
Jonathan: I would like that...

07:07.500 --> 07:08.666
very much.

07:08.701 --> 07:10.001
Barton:
Dinner at my house, then.

07:10.036 --> 07:11.869
I have a '37 Bordeaux

07:11.871 --> 07:15.639
that I've been saving
for just the right occasion.

07:15.675 --> 07:17.091
Jonathan: [ Chuckles ]

07:17.126 --> 07:19.210
Quiet dinner at home.

07:19.212 --> 07:21.779
Perfect.

07:35.395 --> 07:36.527
Libby: Excuse me.

07:36.562 --> 07:38.562
Cindy: You're the neighbor?

07:38.614 --> 07:40.831
Cindy Loman. Sorry
if I don't shake your hand.

07:40.867 --> 07:43.034
I feel like I'm hitting roots
here or something.

07:43.069 --> 07:44.402
Libby: Is Mr. Edley moving?

07:44.454 --> 07:45.786
Cindy: Uh... leave of absence.

07:45.822 --> 07:47.288
He left
like his pants were on fire.

07:47.323 --> 07:49.457
He just told me
to wire him the paperwork.

07:49.492 --> 07:51.409
Libby: Do you know
for how long he'll be...

07:51.411 --> 07:53.244
Cindy: The lease is a year.
That's all I know.

07:53.296 --> 07:55.329
He just told me
that he'd be out of touch,

07:55.381 --> 07:57.148
and to handle the details.

07:57.183 --> 08:00.317
I wouldn't be surprised if I
never hear from that guy again.

08:06.676 --> 08:08.859
Nora: The doors, please.

08:08.895 --> 08:11.429
[ Elevator bell dings ]

08:13.099 --> 08:14.765
Dr. Masters.

08:14.767 --> 08:16.600
William: Nora.

08:16.602 --> 08:21.572
I'm glad-- relieved,
in fact, to see you here.

08:21.607 --> 08:24.108
I wasn't entirely sure...

08:24.160 --> 08:25.860
Nora: That I would show up?

08:28.197 --> 08:34.501
After one unguarded moment in a
dark office between two adults?

08:34.537 --> 08:38.456
We are both adults, aren't we?

08:38.508 --> 08:40.957
William: Of course.

08:40.960 --> 08:44.295
Nora: And both responsible
for our actions.

08:46.349 --> 08:49.900
[ Elevator bell dings,
elevator doors open ]

08:49.936 --> 08:51.635
Dr. Masters,
you must know by now

08:51.687 --> 08:54.138
I take my work here
very seriously.

08:54.190 --> 08:58.692
And I would never just... quit.

08:58.728 --> 09:00.728
William: That's good to know.

09:00.780 --> 09:03.030
We have a-- a full day ahead.

09:03.065 --> 09:04.198
Nora: Oh, apparently.

09:04.233 --> 09:05.399
- [ Thud ]
Betty: - Whoa!

09:05.451 --> 09:07.284
Oh, careful.
Careful, boys.

09:07.320 --> 09:09.537
Linoleum does not grow on trees.

09:09.572 --> 09:11.822
Oh, ah, there you are, doc.

09:11.874 --> 09:13.624
Uh, first, good morning.

09:13.659 --> 09:16.377
Second, I need you to sign off
on these hors d'oeuvres.

09:16.412 --> 09:19.330
For the press conference
tonight.

09:19.332 --> 09:21.832
- For the new book.
Williams: - Oh.

09:21.884 --> 09:23.717
Betty: You arranged
this whole thing in New York.

09:23.753 --> 09:25.719
William: No.
No, we cannot do this now.

09:25.755 --> 09:27.471
Betty: The Little, Brown folks
are already on their way

09:27.507 --> 09:28.556
with publicists
and photographers

09:28.591 --> 09:30.090
and a whole bunch
of fancy reporters.

09:30.143 --> 09:32.510
William: I don't care if Sigmund
Freud risen from the dead is coming.

09:32.562 --> 09:34.395
You need to reschedule this.
Is Virginia in yet?

09:34.430 --> 09:37.515
Betty: No.
And I cannot reschedule this.

09:37.567 --> 09:40.518
And those-- those are
Virginia's messages,

09:40.520 --> 09:42.286
which means they're not <i> yours.</i>

09:42.321 --> 09:43.854
William:
These are all from Dan Logan.

09:43.856 --> 09:45.356
Betty: [ Sighs ]

09:47.276 --> 09:48.909
[ Door closes ]

09:48.945 --> 09:50.961
These words never left my mouth.

09:50.997 --> 09:52.997
But Logan's been calling
Virginia nonstop

09:53.032 --> 09:54.081
the last couple of days,

09:54.116 --> 09:55.799
and she's refusing
to take his calls.

09:55.835 --> 09:59.203
From where I sit,
she's freezing him out.

10:00.373 --> 10:03.090
[ Door opens, closes ]

10:05.978 --> 10:09.430
Gwen: Bye.
Thank you for flying with us.

10:09.465 --> 10:10.714
Bye.

10:10.800 --> 10:13.133
Did you enjoy your stay
in Mexico, Mr. Logan?

10:13.186 --> 10:15.519
Dan: I did not, Gwen.

10:15.555 --> 10:18.489
But it's done.

10:18.524 --> 10:21.225
♪

10:24.146 --> 10:25.279
Virginia: [ Sighs ]

10:25.314 --> 10:27.865
I am in no mood, Mr. Sturgis.

10:27.900 --> 10:29.116
Ronald: Of course you're not.

10:29.151 --> 10:31.785
I am sorry, Mrs. Johnson,
and I do understand.

10:33.539 --> 10:36.574
You need to know--
this is your last chance.

10:36.626 --> 10:38.909
You must get out.
You must act now.

10:38.911 --> 10:41.128
Virginia:
Is that some kind of a threat?

10:41.163 --> 10:42.546
Ronald: Not a threat.

10:42.582 --> 10:44.081
Just save yourself,
Mrs. Johnson.

10:44.133 --> 10:46.083
Do what you need to do.

10:51.507 --> 10:53.474
Virginia: The lawyer
was from the boy's family?

10:53.509 --> 10:54.892
William: Yes.

10:54.927 --> 10:58.729
Mrs. Daughtry's attorney knocked
on our door late at night,

10:58.764 --> 11:01.532
explained that, uh, his clients

11:01.567 --> 11:04.535
might be willing to rescind
their charges against me,

11:04.570 --> 11:07.004
meaning call off
the police investigation,

11:07.039 --> 11:09.240
in return for a check.

11:09.275 --> 11:10.674
Virginia:
Extortion, essentially.

11:10.710 --> 11:12.276
William: Extortion <i> exactly...</i>

11:12.311 --> 11:14.645
Which is why I will fight this
all the way to court.

11:14.680 --> 11:16.914
Virginia: Or you'll pay.

11:16.949 --> 11:18.682
Libby has made it very clear

11:18.718 --> 11:21.585
that she does not want your
family-- Johnny especially--

11:21.621 --> 11:22.886
dragged through the mud.

11:22.922 --> 11:25.289
William: I will not silence
trumped-up allegations

11:25.324 --> 11:28.626
I acted inappro--
inappropriately with a child

11:28.678 --> 11:30.060
by writing a check.

11:30.096 --> 11:33.731
Virginia: Bill, word of this
may have already gotten out.

11:33.766 --> 11:35.799
Ronald Sturgis
just found me in the lobby

11:35.851 --> 11:39.186
and told me to save myself
while I still can.

11:39.221 --> 11:42.640
Now, I know that you
didn't touch that boy.

11:42.642 --> 11:45.476
But these allegations alone
could ruin your reputation.

11:45.478 --> 11:46.477
William: I will not pay.

11:46.479 --> 11:48.779
Virginia:
Damn it, Bill, you <i> will.</i>

11:48.814 --> 11:51.782
Libby and I are aligned on this.

11:51.817 --> 11:53.450
William: - You and Libby?
Virginia: - Yes.

11:53.486 --> 11:56.203
The two people who can see
past your bullheadedness

11:56.238 --> 11:57.955
and actually help you
get through this.

11:59.709 --> 12:05.462
And for the record, the money
cannot come from the clinic.

12:05.498 --> 12:08.565
I will not have
my hard-earned wages

12:08.601 --> 12:11.035
siphoned off to clean up
your personal mess.

12:11.070 --> 12:13.203
Nor will I have
the work sullied,

12:13.239 --> 12:17.041
nor will I let the clinic
be put at risk.

12:34.944 --> 12:38.412
William:
Perhaps you're right.

12:38.447 --> 12:40.998
Perhaps the risk to our work
is too great.

12:41.033 --> 12:44.068
Virginia: Just write the check
so we can get back to work.

12:44.136 --> 12:46.036
William: I can see you're
still upset about New York.

12:46.088 --> 12:47.588
Virginia: I don't want
to talk about New York.

12:47.623 --> 12:49.306
William: I do feel
I-I owe you an apology.

12:49.342 --> 12:50.607
Virginia:
Your apology can wait.

12:50.643 --> 12:52.209
William: Virginia,
I-I just didn't know how else

12:52.244 --> 12:54.845
to prove to you that Dan Logan
is not what he seems.

12:54.880 --> 12:57.765
Virginia: I do not want
to talk about New York.

12:57.800 --> 12:59.600
William: Then we won't.

12:59.635 --> 13:01.101
Virginia: [ Sighs ]

13:01.137 --> 13:04.688
William: I-I understand
there is much to repair here,

13:04.724 --> 13:08.976
both in the clinic
and between us.

13:09.028 --> 13:12.613
But... we've come
through worse trials,

13:12.648 --> 13:14.732
and-- and we will
get through this, as well.

13:14.734 --> 13:17.151
I've also decided,
on our next book,

13:17.203 --> 13:20.504
to remove the "MD"
from my name.

13:20.539 --> 13:21.972
So it is clear to all

13:22.007 --> 13:24.908
that we are perfect equals
in our partnership.

13:24.944 --> 13:27.978
Virginia: You're taking
the "MD" off your name?

13:34.587 --> 13:36.720
The only thing
that matters right now

13:36.756 --> 13:39.923
is protecting the work
and the clinic...

13:39.975 --> 13:42.476
which begins with you writing
the Daughtry family a check.

13:42.511 --> 13:43.927
[ Door opens ]

13:43.929 --> 13:45.179
Betty:
The Little, Brown man is here.

13:45.231 --> 13:47.097
He wants to talk
through tonight's plan.

13:47.099 --> 13:48.565
I know you told me
to reschedule--

13:48.601 --> 13:50.401
Virginia:
We're not rescheduling.

13:50.436 --> 13:53.103
We will go out there,
the two of us together,

13:53.105 --> 13:56.373
championing the work, making it
very clear how pleased we are

13:56.409 --> 14:00.778
to announce our new
and much-anticipated book.

14:00.813 --> 14:02.613
Bob: These reporters

14:02.665 --> 14:04.832
have sat through
a million press conferences,

14:04.867 --> 14:08.168
so instead, we thought, "Why not
take an open-house approach?"

14:08.204 --> 14:11.038
An exclusive tour of
the Masters and Johnson clinic,

14:11.090 --> 14:14.124
right here, on site,
where the magic really happens.

14:14.176 --> 14:16.009
You'll show them
the gadgets, wires,

14:16.045 --> 14:18.262
the whatsits
that make it all work.

14:18.297 --> 14:21.064
Just think of it
as telling a story--

14:21.100 --> 14:24.184
or, better yet,
taking us on a journey.

14:24.220 --> 14:26.603
William: Of our office.

14:26.639 --> 14:29.273
Bob:
No, not just the office.

14:29.308 --> 14:32.893
A journey through one of
today's most fascinating fields

14:32.945 --> 14:35.562
of medical study.

14:35.614 --> 14:38.949
Virginia: Uh... a journey
that began 10 years ago,

14:38.984 --> 14:42.402
when Dr. Masters and I
decided to blaze a trail

14:42.455 --> 14:46.457
into the previously unexplored
arena of human sexuality.

14:46.492 --> 14:48.926
Bob: - Perfect.
- [ Footsteps approaching ]

14:48.994 --> 14:51.328
William:
And here's Mr. Linden.

14:51.380 --> 14:52.830
Another part of our journey.

14:52.882 --> 14:54.264
Lester:
We're going on a journey?

14:54.300 --> 14:55.833
Virginia:
Mr. Linden has documented

14:55.835 --> 14:57.668
the entire trajectory
of our research.

14:57.720 --> 14:59.169
William:
All on film, no less.

14:59.171 --> 15:02.806
A comprehensive account of the
different phases of our study.

15:02.842 --> 15:04.391
Lester: As well
as a comprehensive account

15:04.426 --> 15:05.676
of my own work.

15:05.728 --> 15:09.012
From my early neorealism,
capturing the body as form,

15:09.014 --> 15:11.265
to my more abstract work
of the early 1960s,

15:11.317 --> 15:12.983
measuring the distance
traveled by ejaculate.

15:13.018 --> 15:14.017
Bob: Oh.

15:14.019 --> 15:16.770
William:
And, uh, here's Miss Everett.

15:16.822 --> 15:19.072
She's participating
in our newest initiative--

15:19.108 --> 15:22.359
the surrogacy program,
designed for single men

15:22.411 --> 15:24.077
suffering
from sexual dysfunction.

15:24.113 --> 15:26.029
Bob: You mentioned that
at our meeting in New York.

15:26.081 --> 15:28.765
Very provocative stuff.

15:28.801 --> 15:31.869
Nora: If I may have a moment,
Dr. Masters...

15:31.921 --> 15:33.203
William: Of course.

15:33.205 --> 15:34.271
Excuse us.

15:41.680 --> 15:44.281
Nora, you need to go in there.
Your patient is waiting.

15:44.316 --> 15:45.782
Nora: But how am I
supposed to concentrate

15:45.818 --> 15:46.984
when my landlord is kicking me

15:47.019 --> 15:48.452
and all of my belongings
to the curb?

15:48.487 --> 15:50.921
William: I-I'm happy
to speak to your landlord,

15:50.956 --> 15:52.122
give you a personal reference--

15:52.157 --> 15:53.657
Nora:
He doesn't want a reference.

15:53.692 --> 15:55.459
He wants the rent.

15:55.494 --> 16:00.397
I know that this is wrong,
but...

16:00.399 --> 16:02.616
I don't know who else to ask.

16:02.651 --> 16:05.135
William: I thought
you were getting a job.

16:05.170 --> 16:08.739
Nora: When am I supposed
to look for a job?

16:08.774 --> 16:11.308
I'm here
working six days a week.

16:11.343 --> 16:14.411
Look, I am good at this.

16:14.413 --> 16:16.747
And the last thing that I want
to do is give up the work.

16:16.749 --> 16:19.950
But if it's between that and
having a roof over my head...

16:21.587 --> 16:25.656
I know things are
slightly strained between us...

16:25.691 --> 16:31.094
because of our--
our recent intimacies.

16:31.130 --> 16:34.898
Surely you want
to make things right with me.

16:34.934 --> 16:38.018
William: [ Sighs ]

16:41.273 --> 16:45.659
I will give you another...

16:45.694 --> 16:47.244
$200.

16:47.279 --> 16:48.662
[ Sighs ]

16:48.697 --> 16:50.414
But this has to be
the last time.

16:50.449 --> 16:51.548
Do you understand?

16:51.584 --> 16:54.201
Nora: Thank you.

16:54.253 --> 16:56.036
I won't forget this.

16:58.757 --> 17:01.058
Jane: My job
is to answer all of the mail.

17:01.093 --> 17:04.361
We get upwards of 100-plus every
day from all over the country.

17:04.396 --> 17:05.929
Bob:
Mostly positive, I imagine.

17:05.964 --> 17:09.098
Jane: They run 65% to 75%
negative, give or take.

17:09.134 --> 17:10.800
Bob:
Stay away from statistics.

17:10.836 --> 17:12.836
Jane: Some people
just write in for advice,

17:12.871 --> 17:16.373
and some just to thank
Dr. Masters and Mrs. Johnson.

17:16.407 --> 17:19.643
Just today we got a later
from Fred in Dayton,

17:19.694 --> 17:21.528
who says
that "Human Sexual Response"

17:21.563 --> 17:23.146
actually saved his marriage.

17:23.147 --> 17:25.398
"Before your book,
I thought a clitoris

17:25.483 --> 17:27.416
was something
a woman urinated from.

17:27.453 --> 17:30.354
Now that I understand the
clitoris, what organ in a woman

17:30.389 --> 17:32.456
is responsible for urination,
anyway?"

17:32.491 --> 17:33.624
[ Chuckles ]

17:33.659 --> 17:37.327
And that's actually
how a dialogue begins.

17:37.379 --> 17:39.713
Virginia:
And, uh, for a special treat,

17:39.748 --> 17:42.165
allow me to introduce Dan Logan,

17:42.217 --> 17:45.802
a fellow pioneer and original
investor in our clinic.

17:45.838 --> 17:46.937
Bob: And president

17:46.972 --> 17:49.206
of International Fragrances
and Flavors.

17:49.241 --> 17:50.390
Dan:
Virginia, do you have a moment?

17:50.426 --> 17:53.243
Virginia: Excuse me.

17:57.900 --> 17:59.983
Dan: I would have figured
professing my love

18:00.019 --> 18:01.685
would at least get
my phone calls returned.

18:01.737 --> 18:02.953
Virginia: Dan, I'm sorry.

18:02.988 --> 18:04.604
I-I need...

18:04.657 --> 18:06.690
I need time to think.

18:06.742 --> 18:07.858
A lot has happened.

18:07.910 --> 18:10.193
And honestly,
that was a lot to take in...

18:10.229 --> 18:11.995
in New York.

18:12.031 --> 18:14.331
The laundry list
of your affairs.

18:14.366 --> 18:16.366
And then, of course, your wife

18:16.368 --> 18:17.868
assuring me that you would
never leave her--

18:17.870 --> 18:19.803
Dan: She's no longer my wife.

18:22.474 --> 18:24.107
Mexico is very accommodating

18:24.143 --> 18:25.742
when it comes
to matters of the heart.

18:25.778 --> 18:27.010
And I didn't want this
to fester.

18:27.046 --> 18:29.212
I wanted you to know
I meant what I said.

18:29.248 --> 18:32.933
So I am now officially divorced.

18:32.968 --> 18:37.104
And now I can help you
divorce George,

18:37.139 --> 18:39.473
show you how it works in Mexico.

18:39.525 --> 18:43.060
Virginia:
Dan, I'm sure that...

18:43.062 --> 18:45.395
Divorcing George, that...

18:45.447 --> 18:46.563
that would be the easy part.

18:46.565 --> 18:48.782
It's-- it's everything else.

18:48.817 --> 18:50.617
Dan: Well...

18:53.572 --> 18:56.573
not everything.

18:56.575 --> 18:57.908
One thing.

18:57.910 --> 19:01.712
Virginia, I understand
the hold Bill has on you,

19:01.747 --> 19:04.998
and I can see
how tangled it is with the work.

19:05.050 --> 19:06.550
And I know how much
your work means to you--

19:06.585 --> 19:09.052
Virginia: 'Cause I have put
every ounce of myself

19:09.088 --> 19:10.387
into this clinic.

19:10.422 --> 19:14.725
I have given everything I have,
everything I am to this.

19:14.760 --> 19:17.561
Dan: And I would never ask you
to leave it.

19:17.596 --> 19:22.999
I would ask-- insist, in fact,
that I mean at least that much.

19:27.372 --> 19:31.208
Virginia: [ Sighs ]

19:31.243 --> 19:34.678
Dan, I've been so...

19:34.713 --> 19:37.047
happy...

19:37.082 --> 19:38.782
with you.

19:38.817 --> 19:40.751
But...

19:40.786 --> 19:44.921
But I don't see how you
and the work go together.

19:44.957 --> 19:47.874
I don't ever see
Bill accepting us.

19:47.926 --> 19:49.760
Dan: It's not up to him.

19:49.795 --> 19:52.129
Bill can never make you happy,
not as a man to love.

19:52.131 --> 19:53.630
You know this.

19:53.682 --> 19:55.932
I know this.

19:55.968 --> 19:57.701
Virginia...

19:59.171 --> 20:04.775
I'm here because I love you
and I want you to be my wife.

20:04.810 --> 20:06.226
But I can't run after you,

20:06.278 --> 20:09.646
trying to make you see things
you already know.

20:09.698 --> 20:12.649
That, I can't do.

20:12.651 --> 20:17.287
♪

20:17.322 --> 20:18.955
Barton:
We're pulling out all the stops.

20:18.991 --> 20:20.157
Betty: Oh, yeah.

20:20.159 --> 20:22.459
We're serving roast beef
with horseradish later.

20:22.494 --> 20:24.461
Barton: Oh, I'm making
roast beef myself tonight.

20:24.496 --> 20:27.464
Recipe out
of <i> Ladies' Home Journal.</i>

20:27.499 --> 20:30.083
Betty: Oh.
You're such a gourmand now.

20:30.135 --> 20:32.169
Barton: Yeah, it calls
for a side of mashed potatoes,

20:32.221 --> 20:33.920
but I don't have
any of that fancy equipment.

20:33.972 --> 20:36.723
Do you think
I can substitute boxed potatoes?

20:36.758 --> 20:39.226
It's Jonathan's birthday.

20:39.261 --> 20:42.345
I'm having him over
for a homemade supper.

20:42.397 --> 20:45.232
Betty: Oh, I see.

20:45.267 --> 20:48.435
Um...

20:48.487 --> 20:50.654
was that his idea?

20:52.441 --> 20:53.990
Barton:
Something wrong with it?

20:54.026 --> 20:57.194
Betty: Aside from the fact

20:57.246 --> 20:59.696
that you're hiding this nice
young man in your apartment,

20:59.748 --> 21:02.699
making him watch the boob tube
and eat spuds on his birthday?

21:02.701 --> 21:04.668
Take him out someplace nice

21:04.703 --> 21:07.037
where there's tablecloths
and candles

21:07.089 --> 21:08.705
and they scrape up the crumbs

21:08.707 --> 21:10.707
with those little
bread-crumb scrapers.

21:10.709 --> 21:14.261
Barton: Two grown men
eating a candlelit meal

21:14.296 --> 21:16.379
to celebrate a birthday?

21:16.465 --> 21:18.682
Don't you think
that looks a little, uh...

21:18.717 --> 21:20.350
Betty: Gay?

21:20.385 --> 21:21.818
Wouldn't that be
the end of the world?

21:21.854 --> 21:25.989
I'm making you reservations
around the corner at Vincente's.

21:26.024 --> 21:28.391
You're going.

21:28.443 --> 21:30.560
Bon appétit.

21:35.234 --> 21:38.118
Bob: So, a few candid shots
in here will work--

21:38.153 --> 21:40.987
you at your desk, you on
the phone, you deep in thought.

21:41.039 --> 21:42.906
All very casual,
sleeves rolled up.

21:42.958 --> 21:44.674
William: They can't be candid
if they're planned.

21:44.710 --> 21:47.494
Bob: No one needs to know
how the sausage is made.

21:47.546 --> 21:48.678
I'll take the jacket.

21:48.714 --> 21:49.880
William: I'll keep it on.

21:49.915 --> 21:53.250
Bob:
Dr. Masters, I don't tell you

21:53.252 --> 21:55.635
how to fix a limp willy, do I?

21:55.671 --> 21:58.088
You'll look better
in shirtsleeves.

22:03.312 --> 22:06.396
William:
Oh, my suspenders broke.

22:06.431 --> 22:08.765
Lester: You, um--
you can take my belt.

22:08.817 --> 22:09.933
William:
I don't want your belt.

22:09.935 --> 22:12.652
Bob: You also don't want
your pants falling down.

22:12.688 --> 22:15.505
It's a little too candid.

22:20.812 --> 22:21.845
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

22:21.880 --> 22:23.947
Bob: Tilt the pen
a little to the right.

22:25.984 --> 22:28.785
Now back to the left, I think.

22:31.723 --> 22:32.689
[ Knock on door ]

22:34.626 --> 22:36.593
William: Excuse me...

22:36.628 --> 22:39.296
again.

22:39.348 --> 22:43.016
I didn't realize you'd finished
your session, Mr. Barringer.

22:43.051 --> 22:45.018
Nora should have brought you
to my office

22:45.053 --> 22:47.020
to discuss the next steps
of your treatment.

22:47.055 --> 22:49.723
Hugh: I won't be continuing
with the treatment.

22:49.775 --> 22:52.692
In fact, I'm not here
for the treatment at all.

22:52.728 --> 22:55.729
Dan: Well, what you're
not saying says it all.

22:55.781 --> 22:59.282
Virginia:
The hesitation is not you.

22:59.318 --> 23:01.818
It isn't.

23:01.820 --> 23:06.656
It's all of it.
It's...

23:06.658 --> 23:09.709
Dan: The work.

23:09.745 --> 23:11.828
Well...

23:11.880 --> 23:15.131
The truth is, I am still
very grateful to you.

23:15.167 --> 23:17.937
I was stuck in my marriage
a long time...

23:17.938 --> 23:19.820
years longer than
I ever should have been.

23:21.551 --> 23:25.848
And it was because of you,
because of... my love for you

23:26.671 --> 23:29.722
that I finally
got the courage to leave.

23:30.057 --> 23:34.593
Now I just want to do
the same for you...

23:34.628 --> 23:36.795
Give you the strength to go.

23:36.831 --> 23:42.000
But only if you want me
on the other end of it...

23:42.036 --> 23:44.870
'Cause if not, then...

23:47.875 --> 23:50.943
well...

23:50.995 --> 23:55.047
Then I will take
my broken heart and go.

24:04.391 --> 24:04.823
♪

24:14.852 --> 24:16.018
Virginia: Dan.

24:16.053 --> 24:18.070
Dan.

24:22.977 --> 24:24.776
Bill?

24:24.812 --> 24:26.144
What's going on?

24:26.146 --> 24:28.413
Hugh: I'm glad you're here,
Mrs. Johnson,

24:28.449 --> 24:32.150
'cause this involves you,
as well.

24:32.152 --> 24:35.821
♪

24:38.042 --> 24:39.791
[ Door opens ]

24:41.495 --> 24:42.911
Guard:
Chief Duncan is waiting for you.

24:42.963 --> 24:43.962
[ Lock disengages ]

24:46.634 --> 24:50.736
Sam: The charges are pandering
and promoting prostitution.

24:50.771 --> 24:52.437
Virginia: That's impossible.

24:52.473 --> 24:54.573
Sam: Some religious nut
named Ronald Sturgis

24:54.608 --> 24:56.141
has been down here
for months now,

24:56.176 --> 24:59.077
accusing your clinic
of engaging in illicit work.

24:59.113 --> 25:03.015
The guy's a royal pain, so we
weren't taking him seriously.

25:03.050 --> 25:06.752
But then this complaint about
Bill and a minor child came in,

25:06.787 --> 25:09.021
which added fuel to the fire.

25:09.056 --> 25:10.622
Then the whole thing
went up in flames

25:10.658 --> 25:13.358
when one of your surrogates
came forward to cooperate.

25:13.360 --> 25:15.994
So we were left with little
choice but to file charges.

25:16.063 --> 25:17.696
William:
One of our surrogates.

25:17.748 --> 25:20.699
Virginia: All of our surrogates
are unpaid volunteers.

25:20.701 --> 25:23.335
How could that possibly
be considered prostitution?

25:23.370 --> 25:25.087
I don't understand this.

25:25.122 --> 25:28.790
Bill, do you understand this?

25:30.628 --> 25:32.094
William: Uh...

25:32.129 --> 25:36.048
Nora, uh, got behind with rent.

25:36.100 --> 25:37.099
[ Clears throat ]

25:37.134 --> 25:39.184
So I--
so I gave her some money.

25:39.219 --> 25:40.986
Two times only.

25:41.021 --> 25:43.555
No, but thi--
this can't be what this is.

25:43.607 --> 25:45.607
Nora would-- would never...

25:45.643 --> 25:47.893
I never paid her
for surrogacy work.

25:47.895 --> 25:49.194
Sam:
Well, unfortunately, Bill,

25:49.229 --> 25:50.963
that's now
up to a court to decide.

25:50.998 --> 25:53.231
William: [ Sighs ]
I mean...

25:53.283 --> 25:56.635
A hundred times, she said the
work meant everything to her.

25:56.670 --> 26:00.205
She-- she participated fully
in-- in every aspect.

26:00.240 --> 26:03.575
She-- she was
completely committed.

26:03.627 --> 26:05.911
Sam: Committed
to this Sturgis character,

26:05.913 --> 26:08.213
and the Committee For Decency,
apparently...

26:08.248 --> 26:10.132
I guess in the same way

26:10.167 --> 26:12.417
I've been on your board
of directors for years now,

26:12.469 --> 26:13.752
so you can imagine--

26:13.804 --> 26:16.321
this situation's no picnic
for me, either.

26:16.357 --> 26:17.990
Because you're
under investigation,

26:18.025 --> 26:19.958
I should padlock your doors.

26:19.994 --> 26:22.260
But I don't want to do that.

26:25.232 --> 26:28.767
If this stays out of the press
and between us,

26:28.819 --> 26:30.602
I can buy you some time.

26:30.604 --> 26:32.938
Time for you
to get legal counsel,

26:32.940 --> 26:37.442
sort this out without having to
shut down the clinic entirely.

26:37.494 --> 26:39.411
I'm also trying
to track down Libby

26:39.446 --> 26:40.612
to get you out of here, Bill.

26:40.614 --> 26:43.749
Virginia, your bail's
been posted already.

26:43.784 --> 26:45.817
I'll have a uni
escort you to processing.

26:48.505 --> 26:50.622
[ Door opens ]

26:50.624 --> 26:51.923
William: Virginia?

26:59.233 --> 27:01.967
♪

27:04.638 --> 27:06.138
Dan: Are you all right?

27:06.190 --> 27:07.639
Virginia: [ Sighs ]
Thank God you're here.

27:07.691 --> 27:09.474
Dan: What, you think
I'd let you rot in jail?

27:09.560 --> 27:10.642
Come on.

27:10.694 --> 27:13.945
I'll drop you home
on my way to the airport.

27:13.981 --> 27:16.782
Virginia: Dan...

27:16.817 --> 27:18.700
When you said
that you can't keep trying,

27:18.736 --> 27:20.819
trying to make me see
something that I already know...

27:20.871 --> 27:21.987
Dan: I can't.

27:22.039 --> 27:23.321
Virginia: You're right.

27:23.323 --> 27:28.560
You shouldn't have to,
because I-I do already know.

27:28.595 --> 27:30.996
Ever since I was a little girl,

27:30.998 --> 27:33.915
it's like
I-I've been holding my breath...

27:33.967 --> 27:36.468
waiting for something, something
I can't even put a name to

27:36.503 --> 27:40.138
to fall into place so that
I could finally breathe.

27:40.174 --> 27:42.974
I know you understand this.

27:43.010 --> 27:47.512
But I-I want to... breathe.
I-I do.

27:47.514 --> 27:53.018
I-I want to breathe with you.

27:53.020 --> 27:55.153
I want you.

27:57.324 --> 27:59.691
Dan: Okay.

27:59.693 --> 28:04.329
Virginia:
I-I want to just go.

28:04.364 --> 28:06.531
But I need your help,
and we need to move fast.

28:06.583 --> 28:08.533
Dan: I can move fast.

28:08.535 --> 28:11.837
♪

28:26.053 --> 28:29.054
[ Telephone rings ]

28:29.056 --> 28:30.939
Bob: Why? There's some kind
of medical thing? Is that right?

28:30.974 --> 28:33.592
Betty: Yes, needing
their immediate attention.

28:33.627 --> 28:37.028
Bob: The immediate attention
of two sex researchers?

28:37.064 --> 28:40.499
Betty: If you have to know,
Mr. Drag,

28:40.534 --> 28:46.822
this patient's emergency did
happen to be sexual in nature.

28:46.874 --> 28:49.741
Highly sexual.

28:49.743 --> 28:52.377
Bob: And when do you
expect them back?

28:52.412 --> 28:54.079
Because I have 50 people
coming through those doors

28:54.131 --> 28:55.247
in an hour and a half.

28:55.249 --> 28:58.750
Betty: They should be back
in any moment.

28:58.752 --> 29:01.219
Bob: I'm going back
to the hotel, change,

29:01.255 --> 29:03.255
take some deep, calming breaths.

29:03.257 --> 29:06.391
But when I get back,
they <i> will</i> be here.

29:06.426 --> 29:09.995
Betty: [ Sighs ]
Amen.

29:10.030 --> 29:11.346
Libby: I called the bank.

29:11.398 --> 29:13.348
Mr. Fiske is pulling together
the bail money right now.

29:13.433 --> 29:15.150
William: Good.
I need to get out of here.

29:15.185 --> 29:16.685
Virginia left me
nearly an hour ago.

29:16.737 --> 29:18.069
Libby:
You're worried about Virginia?

29:18.105 --> 29:19.905
William: No.
I mean, yes.

29:19.940 --> 29:22.440
Virginia, the clinic,
you, everything.

29:29.199 --> 29:32.117
The first thing I need to do
is talk to Nora...

29:32.119 --> 29:34.119
Make her admit that the money

29:34.171 --> 29:35.370
was never given
for surrogacy work.

29:35.422 --> 29:36.955
Libby: Do not talk to Nora!

29:37.007 --> 29:38.590
Prostitution charges
are very serious.

29:38.625 --> 29:40.091
William: I know they're serious.
I know.

29:40.127 --> 29:41.343
Libby:
Oh, if you had only listened

29:41.378 --> 29:42.928
when I told you not to hire her.

29:42.963 --> 29:44.462
William: Who knew
we'd hired Judas, Libby?

29:44.464 --> 29:46.264
I-I took that girl
under my wing.

29:46.300 --> 29:48.466
I was-- I was good to her!

29:48.468 --> 29:49.768
I was kind to Dennis.

29:49.803 --> 29:52.270
If I-- if I can just--
if I can just talk to Dennis,

29:52.306 --> 29:54.806
or, at the very least,
reason with his mother...

29:54.808 --> 29:56.541
Libby: You can't reason
with his mother, Bill!

29:56.577 --> 29:59.144
William: I know-- I know I'm a
target now because of what I do,

29:59.196 --> 30:00.562
because the work
is controversial.

30:00.614 --> 30:01.980
Libby: It is not the work!

30:02.032 --> 30:04.649
William: But if I can just
get out ahead of this...

30:04.701 --> 30:06.651
Maybe-- maybe if I help
a press conference...

30:06.653 --> 30:07.986
Libby: My God.
Bill! Bill!

30:07.988 --> 30:10.238
- Listen to yourself, please!
William: - Yeah.

30:10.290 --> 30:13.158
Libby: This happened because of
you, because you are reckless.

30:13.210 --> 30:15.827
I don't say that to be unkind.

30:15.879 --> 30:19.214
Only in the hopes
that something will sink in.

30:19.249 --> 30:22.634
This charging ahead without
thinking of the consequences,

30:22.669 --> 30:25.403
this spinning a million plates
all the time,

30:25.439 --> 30:29.257
trying to control everyone
and everything around you...

30:29.309 --> 30:30.675
Bill...

30:30.677 --> 30:34.346
Honestly,
when is it gonna stop?!

31:10.050 --> 31:12.017
William:
I've been having an affair.

31:15.222 --> 31:16.855
Libby: What?

31:16.890 --> 31:20.492
William: I've been having...

31:20.527 --> 31:23.695
an affair...

31:23.730 --> 31:25.397
for a long time now.

31:25.432 --> 31:27.732
Libby: [ Scoffs ]

31:27.768 --> 31:29.467
[ Laughs ]

31:29.503 --> 31:32.570
William:
With-- with Virginia.

31:32.606 --> 31:34.939
Libby: [ Laughing ]

31:35.008 --> 31:36.541
William:
I'm-- I'm not being funny.

31:36.576 --> 31:37.742
Libby: No.

31:37.778 --> 31:39.794
No, of course not.

31:39.830 --> 31:42.464
Although, to me, because...

31:45.385 --> 31:48.753
I know this, Bill.

31:51.024 --> 31:52.757
William: You-- you know?

31:56.963 --> 31:59.230
How-- how--
how long have you known?

31:59.266 --> 32:01.599
Libby: [ Sighs ]

32:01.601 --> 32:03.435
I have known this for years.

32:03.437 --> 32:06.988
William: Oh, my God.

32:09.609 --> 32:12.077
I'm...

32:12.112 --> 32:14.846
I'm s-- I'm-- I'm so-- so...

32:14.881 --> 32:16.381
Libby: Sorry?

32:18.852 --> 32:20.201
[ Chuckles ]

32:20.253 --> 32:23.788
I do believe you are.

32:23.790 --> 32:26.858
William:
Why didn't you say anything?

32:26.893 --> 32:29.010
For years...

32:29.046 --> 32:30.462
Libby: Well...

32:30.514 --> 32:32.797
William:
How could you live like that?

32:32.799 --> 32:34.349
Libby: Not well.

32:34.384 --> 32:38.136
Um... certainly not easily.

32:38.188 --> 32:42.307
But I made the decision
that our family matters

32:42.359 --> 32:45.777
and our children
matter more than anything.

32:45.812 --> 32:47.345
William: Don't, Lib. No.

32:47.381 --> 32:48.813
- Not more than anything.
Libby: - Oh.

32:48.865 --> 32:50.815
Let's just drop it, okay?

32:50.817 --> 32:53.985
This is not the moment
to hash this out,

32:53.987 --> 32:55.620
when everything is upside down.

32:55.655 --> 33:00.825
William:
Lib, my being with Virginia...

33:00.827 --> 33:03.328
I-I never wanted to hurt you.

33:03.380 --> 33:05.997
If I had known...

33:06.049 --> 33:09.134
how horribly I must have
been making you feel,

33:09.169 --> 33:11.069
that you would accept
so little for yourself--

33:11.104 --> 33:13.304
Libby: Oh, don't say that.

33:13.340 --> 33:15.974
We can-- we can talk later.

33:16.009 --> 33:17.759
William: What, at home?

33:17.811 --> 33:21.212
We just-- we just go home now
and continue like this?

33:21.248 --> 33:22.414
Libby: Oh.

33:22.449 --> 33:24.065
William:
Libby, we can't do this anymore.

33:24.101 --> 33:25.350
This has to be over.

33:25.402 --> 33:26.768
[ Breathes deeply ]

33:26.820 --> 33:30.021
It would be the one honest thing
we've done in years.

33:30.023 --> 33:32.607
You-- you deserve
a real marriage.

33:32.659 --> 33:34.659
I mean,
at least a-- a chance at--

33:34.694 --> 33:36.111
Libby: Bill, stop!
Just stop!

33:36.163 --> 33:39.364
Do not say things
that you cannot unsay.

33:39.366 --> 33:40.532
William:
But when is a good time?

33:40.584 --> 33:42.333
Libby: [ Stomps ]
Oh, for God's sake, Bill!

33:42.369 --> 33:43.868
Why did you have
to open your mouth?

33:43.920 --> 33:47.038
Why-- why did you have to just
let all those things spill out?!

33:47.090 --> 33:48.123
William:
Because it's the truth.

33:48.175 --> 33:49.707
Libby: No!
You do not get to decide

33:49.759 --> 33:52.043
that this is the moment
to end our marriage.

33:52.045 --> 33:55.880
Why on earth
would you say this now?

33:55.932 --> 33:57.098
Because what?

33:57.134 --> 33:59.284
Because you envision
a future with Virginia?

33:59.319 --> 34:02.720
Well, I should warn you, she...

34:02.772 --> 34:05.773
she promised that she
would never take you away

34:05.809 --> 34:06.891
from our family.

34:06.893 --> 34:08.693
We made a pact.

34:08.728 --> 34:10.395
So if you are planning
to run off with her--

34:10.447 --> 34:12.697
William:
You and Virginia made a pact?

34:12.732 --> 34:15.467
Libby: Yes.
Behind your back.

34:15.502 --> 34:18.937
We, um--
we came to an agreement.

34:18.972 --> 34:20.938
William: An agreement.

34:20.974 --> 34:24.324
The-- the two of you.

34:24.377 --> 34:26.478
Without talking to me.

34:26.513 --> 34:30.181
Libby: We took a page
from your own playbook, Bill.

34:30.217 --> 34:31.616
[ Sighs ]

34:37.757 --> 34:41.659
It was the only way that I knew
how to make my family safe.

34:41.695 --> 34:42.760
William: Safe?

34:42.795 --> 34:45.530
Well... we're not safe, Libby.

34:49.235 --> 34:50.268
[ Scoffs ]
Look at us.

34:50.303 --> 34:52.303
No one...

34:52.339 --> 34:53.972
No one is safe.

34:57.077 --> 35:00.912
Libby: You are the biggest fool
that I know.

35:00.947 --> 35:06.701
But much to my heart's regret,
I am the second biggest fool.

35:06.753 --> 35:09.954
Oh, you cannot begin
to understand the things

35:10.006 --> 35:12.357
that I have given up for you!

35:12.392 --> 35:15.593
The happiness that I have turned
my back on for this family!

35:15.629 --> 35:16.861
[ Sniffles ]

35:16.897 --> 35:18.429
William: Libby...

35:18.465 --> 35:19.831
Libby: No.

35:19.866 --> 35:21.683
[ Sighs ]

35:21.718 --> 35:25.203
You'll have to make
other arrangements, Bill.

35:25.238 --> 35:27.171
I will not bail you out.

35:27.207 --> 35:29.474
You cannot come home.

35:29.526 --> 35:32.277
[ Door slams ]

35:45.258 --> 35:49.961
Nora: I know you're angry
and probably confused.

35:49.996 --> 35:52.163
I hope
eventually you'll understand...

35:52.215 --> 35:54.999
and maybe even be grateful.

35:55.051 --> 35:57.802
Virginia:
There are a lot of things

35:57.837 --> 35:59.170
that I could say right now,
Nora,

35:59.222 --> 36:01.673
but "Thank you"
is not one of them.

36:01.675 --> 36:04.342
Nora: I did search my heart
before I did what I did.

36:04.344 --> 36:05.510
I did pray.

36:05.562 --> 36:07.512
Virginia:
Please, leave God out of it.

36:07.514 --> 36:09.681
Nora: We can't leave God
out of anything.

36:09.733 --> 36:11.683
I used to be a lot like you--

36:11.735 --> 36:14.018
unhappy and lost.

36:14.070 --> 36:16.354
And then Ronald told me
about your book.

36:16.406 --> 36:19.107
And when I realized it was
written by someone I knew--

36:19.159 --> 36:21.859
Dr. Masters-- from so long ago,

36:21.861 --> 36:24.696
well, I realized
it must be a sign.

36:24.698 --> 36:28.333
God would never want
something as sacred

36:28.368 --> 36:29.701
as the union
between a man and a woman

36:29.736 --> 36:30.868
to be reduced
to these experiments.

36:30.870 --> 36:32.203
Virginia: Nora, shut up.

36:32.205 --> 36:34.038
You think
that you're doing God's work?

36:34.040 --> 36:38.459
<i>We</i> are the ones
that are saving people...

36:38.511 --> 36:40.211
Giving them hope.

36:40.263 --> 36:43.214
It's people like you,
weak and deluded,

36:43.266 --> 36:47.952
that keep people in the dark,
afraid and lonely and suffering.

36:47.988 --> 36:50.355
So don't talk to me about God...

36:50.390 --> 36:53.691
because as far as I know, God
doesn't want people to suffer,

36:53.727 --> 36:58.029
and yet because of you and
the havoc that you have created,

36:58.064 --> 37:00.098
they will.

37:01.985 --> 37:04.986
Nora: You need
to mend your ways-- unh!

37:09.793 --> 37:12.043
Dan: Betty, I need you
to book those tickets now.

37:12.078 --> 37:14.912
Virginia: And I need you
to excuse my absence tonight.

37:14.964 --> 37:16.664
Betty: Oh.
With The Little, Brown man?

37:16.716 --> 37:18.166
How am I supposed to do that?

37:18.218 --> 37:19.500
Bob: Mrs. Johnson.

37:19.586 --> 37:21.252
I was beginning to think
we'd never see you again.

37:21.304 --> 37:22.420
Virginia: Mr. Drag, yes.

37:22.422 --> 37:25.256
Well, we had an emergency,
but here we are.

37:25.258 --> 37:26.391
Dan: - Mm.
Virginia: - Back.

37:26.426 --> 37:27.425
Bob:
And Bill is back, as well?

37:27.477 --> 37:28.760
Dan: The good doctor's
right behind us.

37:28.812 --> 37:29.761
Bob: Thank God for that.

37:29.813 --> 37:31.012
I was hoping to get some photos

37:31.064 --> 37:32.597
of you two in the lab together,
Mrs. Johnson,

37:32.649 --> 37:34.098
maybe with a dildo
or some beakers.

37:34.100 --> 37:35.350
Dan:
Before you do that, Virginia,

37:35.402 --> 37:36.768
I need you to sign
those papers downstairs.

37:36.820 --> 37:38.069
It's time-sensitive.

37:38.104 --> 37:39.687
Virginia: Yes, of course,
Mr. Logan. I nearly forgot.

37:39.739 --> 37:42.407
I will be back
in just a few minutes.

37:47.280 --> 37:50.832
Betty: Good things
come to those who wait.

37:53.787 --> 37:55.119
Johnny:
Mom, what do you think

37:55.121 --> 37:58.589
of peanut butter and banana
together in a sandwich?

37:58.625 --> 38:01.042
Libby: - [ Crying ]
Johnny: - What's wrong?

38:02.629 --> 38:04.262
Mom, what happened?

38:04.297 --> 38:07.699
Is this about what I said
to get dad in trouble?

38:07.734 --> 38:09.050
Libby: No. No, honey.
Of course not.

38:09.102 --> 38:10.101
[ Sobs, sniffles ]

38:10.136 --> 38:11.436
Johnny: What is it?

38:15.809 --> 38:17.892
Libby: [ Sighs ]

38:17.944 --> 38:22.196
Your father and I
have been talking, and it, uh...

38:22.232 --> 38:26.818
it seems like he's going to stay
somewhere else for a while.

38:26.870 --> 38:28.653
Johnny: S-stay somewhere else?

38:28.655 --> 38:30.621
You mean <i> live</i> somewhere else?

38:30.657 --> 38:33.658
Libby: [ Sighs ]
For a while, yeah.

38:33.710 --> 38:36.060
He and I
have some things to sort out.

38:38.248 --> 38:40.965
Johnny:
S-so you're getting divorced?

38:44.170 --> 38:46.504
[ Sighs ]

38:46.556 --> 38:47.739
I want to talk to him.

38:47.774 --> 38:50.842
Libby: That's gonna be tough,

38:50.894 --> 38:54.512
because he's down
at the police station.

38:54.564 --> 38:56.848
Johnny: He's in jail?

38:56.850 --> 38:58.516
So this is about what I said.

38:58.518 --> 39:00.017
This-- this <i> is</i>
because of what I--

39:00.019 --> 39:01.018
Libby: No. No.
No, no.

39:01.070 --> 39:02.353
It has nothing to do with you.

39:02.355 --> 39:04.021
I promise, okay?

39:04.073 --> 39:05.823
You have to believe me.

39:05.859 --> 39:07.909
And I know--
I know the adult world

39:07.944 --> 39:11.829
can seem incredibly complicated
and unfair

39:11.865 --> 39:14.248
and completely,
completely messed up,

39:14.284 --> 39:17.335
but it has nothing to do
with you, okay?

39:17.370 --> 39:19.036
Your dad is gonna sort out
his problems.

39:19.038 --> 39:20.838
He always does.

39:20.874 --> 39:22.273
[ Sniffles ]

39:34.220 --> 39:38.189
Sam: I'm gonna need
your shoelaces and your belt.

39:38.224 --> 39:40.391
William: I can assure you, Sam,
I'm no threat to anyone--

39:40.426 --> 39:42.393
least of all myself.

39:42.428 --> 39:44.362
Sam: I'm sorry, Bill.
House rules.

39:49.786 --> 39:52.537
♪

40:00.964 --> 40:02.613
Old man: Stay down!

40:04.184 --> 40:06.884
Get on your knees and beg.

40:14.477 --> 40:16.894
Young William: - Aah! Aah!
Sam: - Bill.

40:16.930 --> 40:18.763
Young William: - Aah!
Sam: - Bill.

40:18.765 --> 40:20.565
Young William: - Aah!
Sam: - Bill.

40:22.368 --> 40:24.202
Is there anyone
I can call for you?

40:26.806 --> 40:28.439
William: Virginia.

40:30.109 --> 40:32.994
Barton: Oh, how do Italians
eat like this

40:33.029 --> 40:34.996
and not weigh 300 pounds?

40:35.031 --> 40:36.581
Jonathan: Well, have you
ever been to Rome?

40:36.616 --> 40:38.449
They spend the whole meal
arguing and smoking.

40:38.451 --> 40:40.368
They barely have time
to get a bite in.

40:40.420 --> 40:41.702
[ Both laugh ]

40:41.754 --> 40:43.921
Waiter:
Buon compleanno, signore.

40:43.957 --> 40:45.256
Jonathan: Grazie.

40:45.291 --> 40:46.624
Barton: That's strange.

40:46.626 --> 40:48.359
I didn't tell them
it was your birthday.

40:48.394 --> 40:50.294
Jonathan: I did.

40:50.346 --> 40:53.097
I figured you wouldn't want
to attract attention that way.

40:53.132 --> 40:54.882
On the other hand,
I'm not getting any younger,

40:54.934 --> 40:58.603
so I didn't think it was such
a crime, one little candle.

40:58.638 --> 40:59.737
Barton: Mm.

41:01.641 --> 41:05.042
♪ happy birthday to you ♪

41:05.078 --> 41:11.148
♪ happy birthday,
dear Jonathan ♪

41:11.150 --> 41:13.985
♪ happy birthday to you ♪

41:14.037 --> 41:16.704
[ Chuckles ]

41:16.739 --> 41:18.122
Make a wish.

41:22.879 --> 41:24.495
Jonathan: [ Blows ]

41:26.666 --> 41:28.666
Barton: Oh, excuse me.

41:28.668 --> 41:30.001
Betty: I'm so sorry.

41:30.053 --> 41:31.869
I don't mean to interrupt.

41:31.938 --> 41:36.807
The doc is, uh, in jail,
and I need you to bail him out

41:36.843 --> 41:38.392
so that I can back to the office

41:38.428 --> 41:41.913
and misdirect and confuse
The Little, Brown man.

41:41.948 --> 41:45.650
Please, I need your help.

41:45.685 --> 41:47.685
Virginia: The suitcase
is already packed,

41:47.687 --> 41:49.654
still right where I left it
this morning

41:49.689 --> 41:53.190
when I was going someplace
completely different.

41:53.242 --> 41:54.659
Dan:
Sir, it's been a great pleasure.

41:54.694 --> 41:57.078
I know it's a curious question
to ask, given we just met--

41:57.113 --> 41:58.195
Harry:
Although in five minutes,

41:58.247 --> 41:59.597
you've impressed me enough,
Mr. Logan.

41:59.632 --> 42:02.199
And I'm a pretty quick study.

42:02.235 --> 42:03.534
So you have my blessing.

42:03.586 --> 42:07.288
That is, if it's what
my daughter wants.

42:07.340 --> 42:12.126
Honey, is this what you want?

42:12.178 --> 42:13.778
Virginia: I do.

42:15.548 --> 42:17.131
[ Chuckles ]
Bye.

42:24.474 --> 42:26.324
Dan
[Chuckles]...

42:37.904 --> 42:40.204
[ Telephone rings ]

42:42.291 --> 42:43.774
Barton: Thank you, sir.

42:46.579 --> 42:48.412
Should be another half-hour.

42:48.448 --> 42:52.316
They're pushing through
the paperwork now.

42:52.352 --> 42:55.052
Hell of a thing, Bill.

42:55.088 --> 42:56.420
[ Door opens ]

43:01.861 --> 43:07.264
I'll head back, now that
you're in the works here.

43:07.316 --> 43:10.518
I'm sure you two
could use the time to talk.

43:19.328 --> 43:23.614
Virginia: Bill, before you say
anything, I want you to listen,

43:23.616 --> 43:26.534
because...

43:26.586 --> 43:29.620
Well, because there's
nothing left to be decided...

43:29.672 --> 43:32.857
between us...

43:32.892 --> 43:38.529
or said, even, but I did want
you to hear it from me--

43:38.564 --> 43:40.064
William:
Virginia, I love you.

43:42.635 --> 43:44.268
I always have.

43:47.774 --> 43:54.211
I've loved you so deeply
for the longest time.

43:54.247 --> 43:57.314
I-I could hardly
make sense of it.

43:59.485 --> 44:02.553
God, I should have said this
long ago.

44:02.588 --> 44:06.357
I should have put you first.

44:06.392 --> 44:07.658
[ Breathes deeply ]

44:07.693 --> 44:09.760
And now I can...

44:09.796 --> 44:14.999
because I also believe
deep down

44:15.034 --> 44:17.101
despite our struggles,

44:17.136 --> 44:19.887
despite all-- all this mess,

44:19.922 --> 44:23.674
which I promise
I will make right,

44:23.676 --> 44:27.778
I also believe
that you love me, too.

44:36.906 --> 44:39.090
Virginia: I'm leaving.

44:43.429 --> 44:46.564
I'm flying to Mexico tonight,
and then on to Las Vegas.

44:46.599 --> 44:49.300
William: - No.
Virginia: - Bill...

44:49.335 --> 44:52.970
You're right about me
in many ways...

44:53.005 --> 44:55.506
How I-- how I love the work

44:55.541 --> 44:57.641
and the accomplishments
and the recognition.

44:57.677 --> 44:59.110
But where you're wrong

44:59.145 --> 45:03.547
is thinking that I want those
things in place of happiness.

45:05.818 --> 45:08.219
I want to be happy...

45:08.254 --> 45:11.972
in a life
bigger than-- than work.

45:12.024 --> 45:18.562
I can't be a whole person
without that.

45:18.564 --> 45:22.233
William:
Virginia, I-I can't let you go.

45:22.285 --> 45:25.102
Virginia: You have to.

45:26.939 --> 45:34.778
If you love me
like you say that you do,

45:34.814 --> 45:37.815
you want to put me first.

45:37.850 --> 45:40.584
You won't get in my way.

45:40.653 --> 45:44.221
You'll let me go.

45:44.290 --> 45:46.290
I want to go.

45:58.371 --> 46:00.354
[ Door closes ]

46:02.108 --> 46:04.108
[ Typewriter clacking ]

46:04.160 --> 46:06.577
William: Uh, Masters.

46:06.612 --> 46:08.445
I-I need my, uh, papers now.

46:08.497 --> 46:09.914
Officer: I hear you, sir.

46:09.949 --> 46:12.383
But processing takes
as long as it takes.

46:14.387 --> 46:16.120
[ Clacking resumes ]

46:17.390 --> 46:19.707
[ Indistinct conversations ]

46:22.962 --> 46:25.162
Bob: I have been looking
all over for you.

46:25.198 --> 46:27.865
Betty: I was just finishing up
some work.

46:27.900 --> 46:29.166
Bob: In the dark?

46:29.202 --> 46:31.969
Betty:
I have terrific night vision.

46:32.004 --> 46:33.971
Uh, "Betty the Bat"
used to be one of my Nick--

46:34.006 --> 46:35.973
Bob: I just spoke
with a friend of mine

46:35.975 --> 46:39.026
that works here in St. Louis
in the Police Department.

46:39.061 --> 46:40.477
He thought I'd like to know

46:40.479 --> 46:43.881
that Bill Masters is sitting
behind bars right now.

46:43.916 --> 46:47.551
Betty: Not right now.

46:47.587 --> 46:48.852
No.

46:48.888 --> 46:53.324
He is not in jail <i> currently.</i>

46:53.359 --> 46:54.525
He will be here.

46:54.560 --> 46:56.994
Bob: You know
what my friend also said?

46:56.996 --> 47:00.631
The charges
are pandering and prostitution

47:00.666 --> 47:02.833
and that Dr. Masters
is also being questioned

47:02.885 --> 47:06.570
in relation to improprieties
with a minor.

47:06.606 --> 47:10.574
Betty:
That sounds... not good.

47:10.610 --> 47:12.376
I-I'll admit that.

47:12.411 --> 47:14.745
But none of those charges
are true.

47:14.780 --> 47:19.266
Bob: Let me make myself
very clear, Miss Dimello.

47:19.318 --> 47:21.218
Not only have
I gone out on a limb

47:21.254 --> 47:23.387
to accommodate
Dr. Masters and Mrs. Johnson

47:23.422 --> 47:26.023
every step of the way
with their last book,

47:26.058 --> 47:30.194
but my job is on the line
with this new book, as well.

47:30.229 --> 47:32.129
My bosses at Little, Brown

47:32.164 --> 47:35.616
are not interested
in Masters <i> or</i> Johnson.

47:35.668 --> 47:37.334
The product
they want me to sell,

47:37.370 --> 47:40.921
the product for which they have
already paid a handsome advance,

47:40.957 --> 47:44.208
I might add,
is Masters <i> and</i> Johnson.

47:44.260 --> 47:46.210
In a half-hour,

47:46.262 --> 47:50.130
they are going to be standing
here in matching lab coats,

47:50.182 --> 47:52.299
announcing to the world
that, once again,

47:52.351 --> 47:55.286
they are the cure to mankind's
every sexual misfortune,

47:55.321 --> 48:00.107
or I am going to get
on the stage

48:00.142 --> 48:02.059
and tell those same reporters

48:02.111 --> 48:03.944
that the reason
they aren't there is,

48:03.980 --> 48:07.865
Dr. Masters prefers
spending time with young boys.

48:07.900 --> 48:09.733
That is,
when he and Mrs. Johnson

48:09.785 --> 48:12.036
aren't running a brothel.

48:12.071 --> 48:14.488
Betty:
How about I go now and te--

48:14.540 --> 48:18.292
Bob:
You aren't going anywhere.

48:18.327 --> 48:19.793
[ Telephone receiver clicks ]

48:19.829 --> 48:23.947
You get on the phone,
and you get them back here.

48:32.925 --> 48:35.259
[ Telephone rings ]

48:39.348 --> 48:40.347
Officer: It's for you.

48:41.984 --> 48:43.267
William: Virginia?

48:43.319 --> 48:46.603
It's Betty, and you have got
30 minutes to get here,

48:46.655 --> 48:48.939
or the Little, Brown man
is gonna tell these reporters

48:48.991 --> 48:49.940
why you were in jail.

48:49.992 --> 48:51.358
William:
Why-- why would he do that?

48:51.410 --> 48:54.178
Betty: Because if you <i> and</i>
Virginia don't show up together,

48:54.213 --> 48:56.613
he's gonna lose his job,
and I don't think he's bluffing.

48:56.665 --> 48:58.665
William: [ Sighs ] That wouldn't
just be the end of the book.

48:58.701 --> 48:59.917
That would be
the end of the clinic.

48:59.952 --> 49:02.286
That would be the end
of everything.

49:02.338 --> 49:04.621
Virginia would never
let that happen.

49:04.623 --> 49:07.257
I don't know what you need to do
to get her to come back

49:07.293 --> 49:08.709
or what you need to tell her.

49:08.761 --> 49:09.760
William: I need this.

49:09.795 --> 49:10.861
Officer: You're good to go.

49:10.896 --> 49:12.179
William: All right.

49:12.264 --> 49:13.380
How long at this time of night

49:13.432 --> 49:14.965
will it take me to get
to the Downtown Airport?

49:15.017 --> 49:16.300
Officer: From up here?
20 minutes, tops.

49:16.352 --> 49:17.768
William: All right.
Where can I get a taxi?

49:17.803 --> 49:19.303
Officer: Just out front.

49:25.277 --> 49:26.276
William: Taxi!

49:31.901 --> 49:33.484
Driver: Where to?

49:33.536 --> 49:34.701
William:
The airport, Downtown.

49:34.737 --> 49:36.403
And don't stop for anything.

49:36.455 --> 49:38.155
Driver:
I know all the shortcuts.

49:41.877 --> 49:44.545
♪

49:48.300 --> 49:50.834
[ Woman speaking indistinctly on PA ]

49:54.590 --> 49:58.475
Woman on PA: <i> Flight number 17</i>
<i>for Mexico City, Mexico,</i>

49:58.511 --> 50:01.178
<i>now boarding at gate 4.</i>

50:01.230 --> 50:02.563
<i>Attention, passengers.</i>

50:02.598 --> 50:06.517
<i>Flight 17 for Mexico City,</i>
<i>Mexico, now boarding...</i>

50:06.519 --> 50:08.519
[ Tires squeal ]

50:20.249 --> 50:21.698
William: [ Sighs ]

50:21.700 --> 50:23.834
Woman: Thank you.

50:23.869 --> 50:26.303
Mm-hmm.

50:37.466 --> 50:39.550
Dan:
Are you afraid he's coming?

50:39.602 --> 50:41.685
Or are you afraid he's not?

50:41.720 --> 50:44.721
Virginia: Let's go.

50:44.723 --> 50:47.724
♪

50:51.063 --> 50:53.981
Old man: A man's got to know
when he's beat, son.

50:54.033 --> 50:56.950
A man has got to learn.

50:56.986 --> 51:00.337
Using his head to block
punches-- that's his strategy.

51:00.372 --> 51:02.539
[ Laughs ]

51:03.609 --> 51:07.711
Too damn stubborn or damn stupid
to know when he's beat.

51:07.746 --> 51:10.214
Stay down.
You're beat.

51:20.092 --> 51:21.475
William: Pull over.

51:21.510 --> 51:23.644
Driver: Nah.
We're gonna make it.

51:23.679 --> 51:25.762
William: Pull over anyway.

51:32.488 --> 51:35.489
